IListSession<T>

Represents list session which can be used to sync changes in the list with the database table. E.g. entities from the database can be fetched by using a Spring.Persistence.Core.Session.TSession . After List Session is started, changes can be made in the list (add new entities, remove current entities, change entity properties, etc.). To persist these changes CommitListSession must be called. To clear changes history RollbackListSession must be called.

IRowMapper<T>

Represents interface for mapping rows of a ResultSet on a per-row basis. Implementations of this interface perform the actual work of mapping each row to a result object.
